A manhunt has ensued for a group of community members who are allegedly involved in the attacking of church pastors and congregation outside Polokwane on Sunday.It is alleged that an argument ensued after members of the Devine Church arrived at Ntswaneng Village, finding another group of people in the Church.It is unclear what led to the attack but vehicles, which were parked outside the church, were damaged with stones and others were burnt to ashes.Church members sustained serious injuries and they were taken to the hospital for medical treatment.Police are still investigating the incident and residents have been urged to report any information regarding the incident at #CrimeStop on 08600 10111.-TNA Reporter